item.title: CVE-2018-0983|2024-08-05T03:44:11.821Z -- microsoft%20corporation -- windows%20storage%20services
item.description: Windows Storage Services in Windows 10 versions 1511, 1607, 1703 and 1709, Windows Server 2016 and Windows Server, version 1709 allows an elevation of privilege vulnerability due to the way objects are handled in memory, aka "Windows Storage Services Elevation of Privilege Vulnerability".
